CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 1 reads:"President Kennedy Stumps Area for Democrats - Pitt Field House was jammed with more that 8,000 of the party faithful at the Friday night rally where the Democratic party chief, President Kennedy, roasted the Republicans."
TitMainTitle: President Kennedy addressing crowd in University of Pittsburgh field house with Kennedy portrait and banner for Dilworth for Governor in background
